<item>
            <title>[IO-83] Bug with &apos;df&apos; command on AIX 5.3</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/IO-83</link>
                <project id="12310477" key="IO">Commons IO</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Reported via commons-owner@&lt;br/&gt;
--------------------------------------------&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;From: James Urie&lt;br/&gt;
Sent: Tuesday, July 11, 2006 8:51 AM&lt;br/&gt;
To: &apos;commons-dev-subscribe@jakarta.apache.org&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: New AIX fix?&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;p&gt;Hello,&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;p&gt;I had to change the &quot;commons-io&quot; code to allow for usage on AIX 5.3.&lt;br/&gt;
Attached is the file with changes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The long and short of the change is that the &quot;df&quot; command used in the&lt;br/&gt;
File System Utils classes requires&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A &quot;P&quot; to be added to the switch to enable &quot;POSIX&quot; capability.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;James Urie&lt;/p&gt;</description>
